hostnamectl -- display host information

hostnamectl set-hostname <name>


Basics: 
ls -i  (shows inode information)

ls --full-time 

cp -R /tmp/Invoice/ /home/bob    (copy all contents)

cp --preserve /home/bob/myfile.txt /home/bob/data (preserve attributes)

mv /home/bob/lfcs/* /home/bob/new-data/ (move all contents from the directory, but not the directory itself)

mv /home/bob/new_file /home/bob/old_file (rename a file)

ln -s /tmp /home/bob/link_to_tmp (softlink to /tmp directory inside /home/bob with name link_to_tmp) SOFTLINK

ln /path/to/original/file /path/to/link HARDLINK


mkdir -p /tmp/1/2/3/4/5/6/7/8/9  (create with all non existing sub directories)

FIND:

find $HOME -mtime 0 (modified in last 24hours)
find . -perm 664 (exactly these permissions)
find -perm -664 (at least these permission, will also show higher ones)
find -perm /664 (files / directories with any of these permissions)
find -perm -u+r,g+r (at least owner AND group can read) 
-perm /u+r,g+r (either owner OR group can read)
find . -perm -444 -perm /222 ! -perm /111 (readable by everyone, writable by someone, not executable by anyone)
find . -perm /u+w,g+w ! -perm /o+w (Files writable by either owner OR group, but not by others)
sudo find / -type f ! -perm /4000 (find all files, which have SETUID deactivated)
sudo find / -type f  -perm -4000 (find all files which have SETUID activated)
sudo find / -type f -perm -4000 -delete (delete all files found)
find / -type f -size +1k -exec cp {} /opt/ \; (find all files with size)
find / -type f -size +1M -size -5M (size ranges)
find / -type f -size +1k -not -path "/proc/*" -not -path "/sys/*" (exclude directories from search)


IMPORTANT COMMANDS: 
WRITE TO FILE WITH SUDO PERMISSIONS:

sudo sh -c 'find /opt/findme/ -perm -100 > /opt/foundthem.txt'


CHANGE TIMEZONES: 

chrony or systemd-timesyncd  --- /etc/chrony.conf


